# Swift Testing Standards (MANDATORY - ZERO TOLERANCE)

**ENFORCEMENT**: CI MUST fail on violations. All public APIs MUST have tests. NO exceptions.

## Test Requirements (ENFORCED)

### Coverage Requirements (MANDATORY)

- **ALL public APIs** MUST have unit tests — NO exceptions
- **ALL new/updated functionality** MUST have comprehensive tests
- **Critical paths** MUST have extensive test coverage
- **Test files exempt** from file size limits

### Test Structure (ENFORCED)

- **AAA pattern** — Arrange-Act-Assert structure in every test (MANDATORY)
- **Descriptive names** — `test_behaviorDescription_whenCondition` format (MANDATORY)
- **Test both aligned and unaligned timestamps** for time-sensitive code (MANDATORY)
- **Test edge cases** thoroughly (MANDATORY)

### Test Logger Requirements (ENFORCED)

- **MUST use TestLogger in all tests** — use `TestLogger()` instead of `Logger()` — MANDATORY
- **TestLogger captures log messages** for verification and prevents unexpected log pollution
- **TestLogger is thread-safe** and designed specifically for test environments
- **TestLogger filters expected patterns** to avoid false positives in test pipelines

### Test Performance Requirements (ENFORCED)

- **Individual test duration** — each test MUST complete in less than 10 seconds (MANDATORY)
- **Performance optimization** — tests exceeding 10 seconds MUST be optimized or refactored
- **CI enforcement** — CI MUST fail if any test exceeds 10 seconds

## Test Framework Preference (MANDATORY)

### Framework Selection (ENFORCED)

- **Swift Testing framework is PREFERRED** for new tests — use `@Suite` and `@Test` annotations
- **XCTest framework** is acceptable for existing tests or when Swift Testing is not suitable
- **Mixed frameworks** MUST be in separate test targets to prevent discovery conflicts
- **ModelTraining module** uses split targets:
  - `ModelTrainingTests` — XCTest tests (in `Sources/ModelTraining/Tests/`)
  - `ModelTrainingSwiftTests` — Swift Testing tests (in `Sources/ModelTraining/SwiftTests/`)

### Swift Testing Guidelines (PREFERRED)

- Use `@Suite("Suite Name")` to group related tests
- Use `@Test("Test description")` to mark test functions
- Use `#expect()` macro for assertions
- Struct-based test organization (no class inheritance needed)
- Native async/await support (no `XCTestExpectation` needed)
- Parallel execution by default (better performance)

### XCTest Guidelines (ACCEPTABLE)

- Use `XCTestCase` subclass for test organization
- Use `XCTAssert*` functions for assertions
- Use `setUp()` / `tearDown()` for test lifecycle
- Sequential execution by default

## Test File Location (MANDATORY)

- **Tests in top-level `Tests/` directory** — organized by target name
- **One test target per source target** — each source target MUST have a corresponding test target
- **Target-specific subfolders** — e.g., `Tests/ModelTrainingTests/`, `Tests/SharedTests/`
- **Test files are exempt** from file size limits

### Directory Structure (REQUIRED)

```text
Tests/
├── TargetNameTests/
│   ├── ComponentATests.swift
│   └── ComponentBTests.swift
└── AnotherTargetTests/
    └── SubComponentTests.swift
```

## No Test Skipping (ZERO TOLERANCE)

- **NEVER skip or disable tests** without explicit user instruction
- **Fix failing tests** rather than skipping them
- **Exception**: Metal GPU availability tests for MLX (document explicitly)
- **No silent xfail** — any skip must include reason and removal condition

## Test Quality (MANDATORY)

- **Use candle factories** from `BaseIndicatorComputerTests` for indicator tests
- **Prefer `getMultiValue`** from `IndicatorSnapshot` instead of raw `multiValues` access
- **DRY principle** — reuse test utilities; avoid duplicated setup
- **Inject time/random** — use `DateProvider`/RNG injections for deterministic tests

## Violations (BLOCKED)

- ❌ Public APIs without tests
- ❌ Test files in wrong location
- ❌ Skipped or disabled tests
- ❌ Tests without AAA structure
- ❌ Vague test names not following `test_behaviorDescription_whenCondition` format
- ❌ Tests exceeding 10 seconds execution time
- ❌ Tests using `Logger()` instead of `TestLogger()`

## Enforcement (MANDATORY)

- **Pre-commit hooks**: Verify test coverage, location, and performance
- **CI Integration**: Automated checks fail builds on violations
- **Code review**: Reject PRs with missing tests, violations, or slow tests
- **No exceptions**: All violations must be fixed before merge
